# ðŸ›’ Online Store v2 â€“ Java Console Application

This is the second version of a Java-based console application simulating 
an online shopping platform. Developed as part of the Advanced Programming 
course at the University of Isfahan, this version expands upon the 
foundational features with added functionality, better exception handling, 
and a more modular architecture.

---

## ðŸš€ Key Features

- **Role-based system:** Admin, Seller, and Buyer accounts
- **Product catalog:** Multi-category system with category-specific fields 
(e.g., electronics, clothing)
- **Product comparison:** Uses `Comparable` interface to sort by type, 
name, rating, price, and stock
- **Warranty system:** `WarrantyCapable` interface with custom logic for 
digital and home appliances
- **Discount engine:** Create and apply time-limited, capacity-based 
discount codes
- **Exception management:** Custom exception classes for invalid input, 
purchase errors, and discount misuse
- **Admin control panel:** Validate sellers, manage users, track all 
discount codes
- **Seller tools:** Add/edit products, apply discounts, manage inventory
- **Buyer tools:** Add to cart, apply discount codes, complete purchases 
with validation

---

## ðŸ§° Technologies Used

- **Language:** Java (JDK 8+)
- **IDE:** IntelliJ / VS Code / NetBeans
- **Version Control:** Git (Phase committed to branch `main` or `2_Phase`)
- **Interface:** Text-based / Console-driven
- **Structure:** OOP with modular package layout

